      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ISLA ROCHELLE (6) has been in terrific form with a series of wins and placings at Menangle. Made it two wins on the trot when she drew wider and worked but beat the mares by 3.4 metres last time. Races well here and winning form is hard to knock. PERFECT STRANGER NZ (5) is a talented gelding first up from a break of three-and-a-half months but generally wastes no time finding form, winning two of three previous fresh attempts. Was very consistent in the city last time in. Gives fitness away to the to pick but he was readied with a trial and is unbeaten here. DAY TWO (7) was rewarded for his recent consistency when he scored from a similar draw at this circuit and distance last time. Go well along with KIMCANDO (4) who was down the track in the city last time but placed the last two times she raced here.",
